The custom built X-ray vault found within the lab allows for the visualization of fluid flows in opaque systems. 
A video introduction to the lab and equipment can be found on the College of Engineering Youtube channel and is linked below.
This lab is run by Ted Heindel, Bergles Professor of Themal Science at Iowa State University.

Hi everyone. I’m Richard Nomad, the creator behind Relaxation Film.

This channel offers long form 4K nature films crafted for immersive viewing on Smart TVs and large screens. Whether it’s forests, mountains, oceans, or wildlife, every scene is chosen to evoke a sense of calm, wonder, and connection to Earth.

Some footage is recorded by me using Sony A6400, A7siii, DJI Mini 3 Pro, with lenses ranging from 18–105mm to 400mm. Others are licensed or carefully sourced to complete the story when I can’t physically be there.

Music: Gentle piano, ambient textures
Sound: Raw audio captured from real jungles — birdsong, insects, wind, water

Relaxation Film features seasonal journeys, forest escapes, winter silence, ocean stillness, and dreamlike ambient soundscapes.

This channel is made for deep rest, focused work, meditation, and peaceful sleep — best enjoyed on Smart TVs or during quiet moments.

Thank you for being part of this journey.
A Relaxation Film Original by Richard Nomad
